transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling. This is John. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi there. I'm trying to get a hold of Angel. Does he still work there?

Speaker 1: He's been out. He works here, but he's been out. What can I help you with, sir?

Speaker 2: Well, I had an order pending with him for, I thought, 60-20 mg Cialis every 5 months.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Well, I got an order in today from Kentucky for only 30-20 mg Cialis.

Speaker 1: So, is the RX number, would that help you?

Speaker 2: No, your name and zip code does, though.

Speaker 1: Pardon?

Speaker 2: Your name and zip code helps me.

Speaker 1: Richard Richards, 8003.

Speaker 2: Okay. Gray Street?

Speaker 1: Arvada, Colorado.

Speaker 2: Okay. I don't see a note about that, but I will have them send you another 30.

Speaker 1: You don't see that he set that agreement up?

Speaker 2: I see that he changed the frequency for you, and it is Cialis, but I see he has it set at 30.

Speaker 1: I don't see a note that he said it should have been 60.

Speaker 2: When did he change it?

Speaker 1: You switched over from 24 pills to 30 at the end of December 2024.

Speaker 2: But you don't show anything for us?

Speaker 1: We don't have a 60 pack, so that's why I, like, I mean, I, like, I don't know what agreement you came to,

Speaker 2: because I don't doubt that you spoke to him, because I see he has notes in here about your orders,

Speaker 1: but we don't even do a 60 pack usually, so I'm not sure what happened with that.

Speaker 2: Well...

Speaker 1: But he did give you a much better price on the 30 than normal,

Speaker 2: because normally 30 pills is like $200, and he's only charging you $108.

Speaker 1: Well, you know, I'm older, so I must be mistaken about that for some dumb reason.

Speaker 2: In fact, I thought it was 30, I thought it was 60 every five months, and you're showing it's 30 every five months.

Speaker 1: Yes, sir, but I do see he gave you a better price, so maybe that's what the compromise was.

Speaker 2: Maybe you had wanted more pills, but he said, I can give this to you at a cheaper price or something.

Speaker 1: That may have been what the deal was, because he's giving you a deal on your price here.

Speaker 2: So what's the normal price for 30?

Speaker 1: It's like $214, you're getting it for $108.

Speaker 2: Really?

Speaker 1: Yes, so he definitely set you up well with the pricing.

Speaker 2: If you want me to change the frequency, I can.

Speaker 1: If you want it a little more often, I can do that.

Speaker 2: Otherwise, I can keep it every five months, if that's what you want.

Speaker 1: Okay, for now, let's leave it as is.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'm sure I'm the one making the mistake here.

Speaker 2: I'm glad you called and we could talk that out, though, so at least you know you can get a deal.

Speaker 1: Sometimes I forget what I had for lunch yesterday.

Speaker 2: It's okay, sir.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: My mistake here.

Speaker 1: No problem.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a good day.

Speaker 1: All right, thank you.

Speaker 2: Bye.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
